The paper deals with distributed algorithms for agreement problems in asynchronous systems, which are typically studied in the Distributed Computing (cs.DC) and Distributed Systems (cs.DS) sub-categories. The use of atomic read/write registers only suggests a focus on shared memory algorithms, which is also relevant to the Programming Languages (cs.PL) sub-category. The paper also involves lower and upper bounds on the number of registers needed to solve the problem, which is related to the Logic in Computer Science (cs.LO) sub-category. Finally, the repeated version of the problem is addressed, which is a common topic in the Distributed Computing community.
